@0h energy and thus power can be reduced
by lowering the voltage
@0i voltage lowering occured with each new generation
of tech
@0j power is function of voltage squared. $P=V^2$
@0k 20 years, voltage has gone from 5v -> 1v, hence power
increase 30x
@0l problem today: further lowering of voltage makes
transistors too leaky
@0m 40\% power consumption due to leakage
@0n to address power problem, designers add large devices
to increase cooling
@0o static cenergy consumption occurs because of leakage
current, even when a transistor is off
@0p increasing number of transistors increases power
dissipation, even when transistors are off
@0q why is power a challenge for IC? @0r power must
be brought in and distributed around chip
@0s power is dissipated as heatand must be removed
@0t microprocessor vs processor
@0u processors = "cores"
@0v microprocessors = multicore microprocessors
@0w "quadcore" microprocessor: chip that contains
4 processors/cores.
@0x since 2006, companies ship microprocessors
with multiple processors per chip
@0y benefit: often more on throughpu than response time
@0z programmers now need to improve response time
in programs by rewrite to take advantage of
multiple processors
@10 why is it difficult for programmers to explicitly
write parallel programs?
@11 parsing is by definition performance programming,
which increases difficulty
@12 fast for parallel hw means programmer must divide
app so that each processor has roughly same amount to
do same time, overhead of scheduling/coordinatoin doesn't
"fritter away" perf benefits of parallel
